.TH "page_add_new_anon_rmap" 9 "page_add_new_anon_rmap" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
page_add_new_anon_rmap \- add pte mapping to a new anonymous page
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" page_add_new_anon_rmap
.BI "(struct page *page "  ","
.BI "struct vm_area_struct *vma "  ","
.BI "unsigned long address "  ","
.BI "bool compound "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "page" 12
the page to add the mapping to
.IP "vma" 12
the vm area in which the mapping is added
.IP "address" 12
the user virtual address mapped
.IP "compound" 12
charge the page as compound or small page
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Same as page_add_anon_rmap but must only be called on *new* pages.
This means the inc-and-test can be bypassed.
Page does not have to be locked.
